<br>
Ok here is how it goes..<br>
This is an idea for a quest..<br>
We STORM (&lt;--- the operative word in the sentence) a dungeon of choice, dont know many so i will use splitpaw as an example. By storming we will attack, charge and kill things in the dungeon at an amazing speed. Hence we will require alot of brave Victus Fortis souls. Many of groups will be formed and when a one dies we leave to be and continue the storming. The dead will be celebrated later.<br>
However the main point to the storming is to get to the epicentre of the dungeon to kill a named creature of choice.. what say Tesch Val Kadvern from Splitpaw.. I will tell you the reason for this later..<br>
The Rules for this quest are that we are under a time constrait of 30-60mins (&lt;--- completly arbitrary) hence the storming to kill the target/mark/or whathaveyou.<br>
anather rule is that each individual will be outfitted with 4 stacks of alcoholic beverages of choice (wine, beer, or even ughhh fish wine) [reason for this will be stated later] and for the duration of the 30-60mins of combat each individual have to finish drinking the 4 stacks of alcoholic beverages of choice.<br>
<br>
<br>
Ok now your wondering &quot;FOR GOD's SAKE MAN WHY&quot;<br>
cause this will be fun.. and itd be nice to roleplay..<br>
<br>
StoryLine behind this..<br>
The members of the proud and brave guild VICTUS FORTIS have been poisoned! by an opposition clan (eg splitpaw). Our GUILDMASTER has died! We want vengence! But we have a limited time (30-60mins RL) as the poison seeps though our systems and we are all dying.. (hence the reason for the alcohol =&gt; to create the impression of a poisoned self which has similar effects to being drunk <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  or to rolplay mindfeebling effects, a player can control the peaks and lows of teh effect by the amount he/she drinks to simulated the effect of being poisoned) those who wish not to participate we can consider dead for roleplaying reasons and reasons for vengence. But the main fact is clear we are angry and want to exact vengence on the person in charge of poisoning all of us (our target of choice).<br>
